com.xilinx.rapidwright.design

Class Design

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.Design
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Design
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The Design class is the central location that maintains the physical netlist and has hooks and references into the logical netlist. Ideally, this class holds all the information necessary to reproduce a design in Vivado.
    See Also:

      • readCheckpoint

        public static Design readCheckpoint(java.lang.String dcpFileName)
        Reads a design checkpoint file into a design object. It will attempt to parse the EDIF inside the DCP if it is not encrypted. If it is encrypted, it will look in the same directory as the DCP for an EDIF file of the same name (ex: mydcp.dcp --> look for mydcp.edf). If that file is not present or encrypted, it will cause an error.
        Parameters:
        dcpFileName - Name of the DCP to load.
        Returns:
        A new design object of the design loaded from the DCP.

      • readCheckpoint

        public static Design readCheckpoint(java.lang.String dcpFileName,
                                    CodePerfTracker t)

      • readCheckpoint

        public static Design readCheckpoint(java.lang.String dcpFileName,
                                    java.lang.String edfFileName)
        Reads a design checkpoint file into a design object. It will use the provided edfFileName to parse the netlist and ignore the EDIF file inside the DCP.
        Parameters:
        dcpFileName - Name of the DCP file to load.
        edfFileName - Name of the external EDIF file to load.
        Returns:
        A design object loaded from the provided files.

      • readCheckpoint

        public static Design readCheckpoint(java.lang.String dcpFileName,
                                    boolean skipXdef)
        Reads a design checkpoint file into a design object. It will attempt to parse the EDIF inside the DCP if it is not encrypted. If it is encrypted, it will look in the same directory as the DCP for an EDIF file of the same name (ex: mydcp.dcp --> look for mydcp.edf). If that file is not present or encrypted, it will cause an error.
        Parameters:
        dcpFileName - Name of the DCP to load.
        skipXdef - Flag to indicate if the XDEF (placement and routing information) file should be loaded.
        Returns:
        A new design object of the design loaded from the DCP.

      • placeCell

        public boolean placeCell(Cell c,
                         Site site,
                         ElementType bel)
        This is a limited checking placement method for placing a cell on a BEL site. The rule set is somewhat complicated to place a cell into a site and this function does not address many of those rules. The caller is responsible for checking/updating appropriate pin mappings from cell pins to BEL site pins. Only a generic set of pin mappings is provided via the UnisimManager.
        Parameters:
        c - The cell to be placed.
        site - The site containing the BEL to be placed.
        bel - The BEL site onto which the cell placement is attempted.
        Returns:
        True if the placement was successful, false otherwise.

      • placeCell

        public boolean placeCell(Cell c,
                         Site site,
                         ElementType bel,
                         java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> pinMappings)
        This is a limited checking placement method for placing a cell on a BEL site. The rule set is somewhat complicated to place a cell into a site and this function does not address many of those rules. The caller is responsible for providing pinMappings.
        Parameters:
        c - The cell to be placed.
        site - The site containing the BEL to be placed.
        bel - The BEL site onto which the cell placement is attempted.
        pinMappings - The physical to logical pin mappings for the cell.
        Returns:
        True if placement was successful, false otherwise.
